<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-63-0969 </DOCNO><TEXT>Home Oil, a medium sized Canadian oil and gas company, has gone througha major redevelopment phase of its computer system, with the major emphasison development of online corporate database systems. Integrated informationsystems are also seen as a beneficial part of this redevelopment. Progressis being made in reducing the volume of paper generated within the company,in the gradual use of personal computers within the system largely basedon mainframes, in development of data acquisition from remote sites,in the linking up of departmental databases to provide increased databaseintegration, and to provide better security to confidential data, end-usertraining, and increased office automation.</TEXT></DOC>